416 LITERAE PAPALES.

CCCCXXXVII. Mandate by clement VII. to the bishops of Oaserta and Aberdeen, md to Gilbert Strathauchin, canon of Aberdeen, to induet James Pitcairn into the corporal possession of the arehdeaconry of Breeffin, to which the Pope had presented him, on the resignation thereos by David Etenim, the former archdeacon. Dated at St. Petet-s, in Rome, Sth October, in the third year of the Pope's pontificante, 1526.
